üçÉ I am focused on progress not perfection üôè I think today was the first day I felt a synchronicity between my breath and movements--couldn't distinguish one from the other! When I woke up today to get ready for weight training, my body was in a bit of a funk, and combined with the disappointment of missing practice yesterday, I was going to force myself to go lift to clear my mind. But over the weekend, my mind and body were both recovering and going through their own individual healing processes; so I realized maybe I need to slow my roll because it's only been like two months, and I'm trying to do everything again! Health and emotional growth (and I guess life in general) are seldom linear, and sometimes I forget that when I get momentum in different areas of my life. This practice really helped flush out my mind and body, and practice is done. So I mean, practice is done, I feel tons better and I am reminded not to be a slave to my momentum or perfection, because the former can be blinding and controlled and the latter is an ideal that isn't real. Namaste üôè
